@modus:root:/ 12> help *report_scanchains*
Commands:
    report_scanchains:

    report_scanchains is used to perform the tracing and reporting of scan path 
    for the specified scan chain(s).


report_scanchains:

 [-H]                                  Help text
 [-h]                                  Help text
 [-LOG no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to Log
 [-LOGCOMPRESS yes|no] (no)            Compress the log file
 [-LOGFILE <outfilename>]              Write to specified log file
 [-STDOUT no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to STDOUT
  -TESTMODE <string>                   Test Mode Name
  -WORKDIR <string>                    Working Directory
 [-bitids <integer 1 or greater>]      Specify the bit positions in the specified scan chain to perform the tracing.
 [-cellinternal yes|no] (Conditional Default) Report the nets, blocks and pins within the technology cell.
 [-chainids all|<integer>1:[,all|<integer>1:]...] (all) Specify the list of observable chain numbers to perform the scan chain tracing. Specify 'all' to trace all the observable scan chains in the design.
 [-coreinstance <string>]              Specify active migrated core instance name or Id for Hierarchical Test run.
 [-coreswitching yes|no] (no)          Switch to core for scan chain tracing.
 [-exportcsvfile <outfilename>]        Filename of the trace report csv file.
 [-exportdirectory <outdir>] (testresults/logs) Specify the location of the directory to store the output files.
 [-help <string>]                      Help Facility
 [-hiertrace yes|no] (no)              Specify 'yes' if reported trace should contain all hierarchical blocks, or just the cell/primitive blocks.
 [-indent yes|no] (yes)                Indent the tracing report according to the depth level.
 [-messagecount <string>]              Limit Messages for Specified Message Id (e.g., messagecount=XXX-710=3).
 [-messagecounteach <integer>]         Default Limit for Each Message.
 [-messagecounteachseverity all|excludeinfo] (all) Level of severity for which messages are to be suppressed as per messagecounteach
 [-reportblocks yes|no] (yes)          Report the blocks encountered during tracing of the specified scan chains.
 [-reportchains yes|no] (yes)          Report Observable Scan Chains Statistics
 [-reportcircuit yes|no] (no)          Report Circuit Statistics
 [-reportdesigncellsummary yes|no] (Conditional Default) Report the summary of technology cells within the design.
 [-reportnets yes|no] (yes)            Report the nets encountered during tracing of the specified scan chains.
 [-reportpins yes|no] (yes)            Report the pins encountered during tracing of the specified scan chains.
 [-stylusnames yes|no] (Conditional Default) Use the CUI naming convention for block types.
 [-traceallcores yes|no] (no)          Specify 'yes' if all cores in the hierarchical design should be traced.
 [-tracereport yes|no]                 Generate the trace report csv file.

